result.execSummary:
The defendant Austin C. Lashbrook was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt:
10:43am Cases called: 21CT308, 22CF692, 22CF546, 22CM294. Defendant Austin C. Lashbrook appeared by video, in custody from the Wright County Jail.  Attorney Zebulon Patek in court for Austin C. Lashbrook.  Attorney Andrew Gunderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Parties have an agreement. State in compliance with victim notification requirements. Defendant waives his right to appear in person. Defendant waives reading of Information in the felony files and enters Not Guilty pleas. 

Defendant enters a no contest plea to:
Count 1 in 21CT308: Operate with Restricted Controlled Substance (2nd)
Count 2 in 22CF692: Felony Bail Jumping as a repeater
Count 1 in 22CF546: Battery By Prisoners as a Repeater
Count 4 in 22CF546: Criminal Damage to Property as a Repeater

Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. Court accepts the pleas and finds the defendant guilty. 

21CT308: Court orders fine and costs of $1,429, 10 days jail, 12 months driver's license revocation, 12 months ignition interlock device, AODA and driver safety plan. 8 days of jail credit.

Court orders on the below counts all concurrent to each other: 
Count 2 in 22CF692: Felony Bail Jumping as a repeater - 3 years Probation sentence withheld with conditions, but consecutive to any other sentence.
Count 1 in 22CF546: Battery By Prisoners as a Repeater - 3 years Probation sentence withheld with conditions, but consecutive to any other sentence.
Count 4 in 22CF546: Criminal Damage to Property as a Repeater - 1 years Probation sentence withheld with conditions, but consecutive to any other sentence.

Conditions of Probation: 
$2,200 Restitution plus 10% surcharge in 22CF546
$1,540 Restitution plus 10% surcharge from 22CM294 to be added to 22CF546
court costs and surcharges
Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. 
Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations including anger management classes.
90 days jail on each count concurrent. 
Maintain absolute sobriety. 

Anything else in these files including citations and all of 22CM294, is ordered dismissed and read in or merge as appropriate.
Order Approving Defense's request to withdraw Request for Substitution of Judge.
Dated 08/17/2022, Request from Attorney Zebulon Patek to withdraw the request for substitution of judge.
Defendant's Request for a Substitution of Judge

9:35 AM case called. Prosecuting Attorney Kelly Ronquist in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Austin C. Lashbrook in court, in custody with Attorney Zebulon Patek. Defendant waives right to a preliminary hearing and Court accepts waiver. Branch 4 for scheduling Arraignment.
